President Obama has nominated Abdul K. Kallon and Jacqueline H. Nguyen to serve on the District Court bench. Abdul Kallon is currently a partner at Bradley Arant Boult Cummings in Birmingham, Alabama, specializing in labor and employment law. He graduated from Dartmouth College in 1990 and the University of Pennsylvania Law School in 1993. He previously clerked for Judge U.W. Clemon of the U.S. District Court for the Northern District of Alabama and is a past president of the Board of Directors of the Legal Aid Society of Birmingham. Judge Jacqueline Nguyen is currently a Superior Court Judge for the County of Los Angeles. She received her undergraduate degree from Occidental College in 1987 and her law degree from the University of California at Los Angeles in 1991. She worked in private practice specializing in civil litigation before becoming an Assistant U.S. Attorney in the Central District of California. She is being nominated to the United States District Court for the Central District of California. Both nominees were rated well-qualified by the ABA. President Obama expressed confidence that they will serve the American people well and is honored to nominate them.